 </disp-formula> This expression helps us to determine (in a prescriptive way) whether the process is governed by stochasticity (
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sup>2</sup> → 0) or by parametric variability (
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sup>2</sup> → 1). Also, as it can be expected, the variance at shorter times is governed by pure random fluctuations but as time proceeds, parametric variance, if present, is increasingly more relevant. We plot 
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sup>2</sup> as a function of time in Figure 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">2</xref>
</p>
